# 📋 Detailed Findings Report
## Bitcoin Fear & Greed vs Hyperliquid Trader Performance

**Dataset:** 211,224 trades · 32 traders · 246 coins · May 2023 – May 2025  
**Analysis date:** May 2025

---

## 1. Data Overview

The dataset covers two years of live trading activity on the Hyperliquid decentralised exchange, merged with the daily Bitcoin Fear & Greed Index. Each trade is classified under one of five sentiment regimes based on the index value on that trading day.

| Regime | Index Range | Trades | % of Total |
|---|---|---|---|
| Extreme Fear | 0–24 | 21,400 | 10.1% |
| Fear | 25–44 | 61,837 | 29.3% |
| Neutral | 45–55 | 37,692 | 17.8% |
| Greed | 56–74 | 50,303 | 23.8% |
| Extreme Greed | 75–100 | 39,992 | 18.9% |

**Observation:** Fear dominates (29.3%) — consistent with Bitcoin's historical tendency to spend more time in bearish sentiment. Extreme Fear is rarest (10.1%), suggesting it is a short-lived but intense regime.

